  "summary": "Castleman disease (CD) is a group of rare lymphoproliferative disorders characterized by enlarged lymph nodes, a broad range of inflammatory symptoms, and laboratory abnormalities. It can involve one or more enlarged lymph nodes in a single region (unicentric CD, UCD) or multiple enlarged lymph node regions (multicentric CD, MCD).",
